 so let's begin then with"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:45:18.872","End":"2025-02-10T14:45:19.122","Content":"Senate 21. If you're ready to"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:45:21.475","End":"2025-02-10T14:45:21.725","Content":"go, um, we have, we do see real"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:45:22.843","End":"2025-02-10T14:45:23.093","Content":"quick on the opponents or"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:45:24.578","End":"2025-02-10T14:45:24.828","Content":"proponents. I want to thank"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:45:27.214","End":"2025-02-10T14:45:27.464","Content":"everybody in the room and, and"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:45:29.616","End":"2025-02-10T14:45:29.866","Content":"paying attention to our, our"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:45:30.217","End":"2025-02-10T14:45:30.467","Content":"committee rules."},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:45:32.853","End":"2025-02-10T14:45:33.103","Content":"Um, and honoring those committee"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:45:33.62","End":"2025-02-10T14:45:33.87","Content":"rules. So we have a number of"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:45:38.559","End":"2025-02-10T14:45:38.809","Content":"people registered in opposition"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:45:41.095","End":"2025-02-10T14:45:41.345","Content":"and um and then organizations in"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:45:42.796","End":"2025-02-10T14:45:43.046","Content":"support, which I'll, I'll read"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:45:44.765","End":"2025-02-10T14:45:45.015","Content":"through center work but uh go"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:45:45.399","End":"2025-02-10T14:45:45.649","Content":"ahead and you've got um"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:45:47.501","End":"2025-02-10T14:45:47.751","Content":"Experts and you've got 15"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:45:48.068","End":"2025-02-10T14:45:48.318","Content":"minutes."},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:45:51.071","End":"2025-02-10T14:45:51.321","Content":"Are you wanting to reserve"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:45:51.638","End":"2025-02-10T14:45:51.888","Content":"anything at all?"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:45:53.373","End":"2025-02-10T14:45:53.623","Content":"No, I think it's important to."},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:45:55.309","End":"2025-02-10T14:45:55.559","Content":"Yeah, reserve a couple of"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:45:57.01","End":"2025-02-10T14:45:57.26","Content":"minutes and I want and I wanna"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:45:58.612","End":"2025-02-10T14:45:58.862","Content":"make sure because I think I"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:45:59.346","End":"2025-02-10T14:45:59.596","Content":"also, it's important to explain"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:46:01.348","End":"2025-02-10T14:46:01.598","Content":"what the sub does up front,"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:46:02.783","End":"2025-02-10T14:46:03.033","Content":"because I think a lot of the"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:46:04.551","End":"2025-02-10T14:46:04.801","Content":"opposition, quite frankly, is"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:46:05.285","End":"2025-02-10T14:46:05.535","Content":"going to go away once they hear"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:46:05.953","End":"2025-02-10T14:46:06.203","Content":"what's in the sub."},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:46:08.555","End":"2025-02-10T14:46:08.805","Content":"Uh, so I'm gonna do both. So let"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:46:10.557","End":"2025-02-10T14:46:10.807","Content":"me just jump in. Uh, thank you"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:46:12.526","End":"2025-02-10T14:46:12.776","Content":"for hearing Senate Bill 21 and"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:46:15.062","End":"2025-02-10T14:46:15.312","Content":"22, uh, these are sponsored by"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:46:16.563","End":"2025-02-10T14:46:16.813","Content":"myself, Representative Ortez,"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:46:18.866","End":"2025-02-10T14:46:19.116","Content":"and Senator Gonzalez with me"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:46:19.5","End":"2025-02-10T14:46:19.75","Content":"today from the New Mexico"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:46:21.235","End":"2025-02-10T14:46:21.485","Content":"Environment Department Service"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:46:21.935","End":"2025-02-10T14:46:22.185","Content":"Water Quality Bureau."},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:46:25.339","End":"2025-02-10T14:46:25.589","Content":"Chief Shelley Lemon and counsel,"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:46:27.174","End":"2025-02-10T14:46:27.424","Content":"general counsel Zach Ogas."},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:46:31.245","End":"2025-02-10T14:46:31.495","Content":"Uh, so Senate Bill 21 lays the"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:46:33.013","End":"2025-02-10T14:46:33.263","Content":"groundwork for the environmental"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:46:34.548","End":"2025-02-10T14:46:34.798","Content":"environment department to"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:46:35.315","End":"2025-02-10T14:46:35.565","Content":"implement the federal Clean"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:46:37.317","End":"2025-02-10T14:46:37.567","Content":"Water Act in New Mexico,"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:46:39.319","End":"2025-02-10T14:46:39.569","Content":"including permitting compliance"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:46:41.355","End":"2025-02-10T14:46:41.605","Content":"and enforcement. This is a"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:46:43.023","End":"2025-02-10T14:46:43.273","Content":"federal statute that's been in"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:46:43.657","End":"2025-02-10T14:46:43.907","Content":"place since 1972."},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:46:48.796","End":"2025-02-10T14:46:49.046","Content":"Uh, what this bill does is give"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:46:51.098","End":"2025-02-10T14:46:51.348","Content":"New Mexico and New Mexicans"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:46:53.367","End":"2025-02-10T14:46:53.617","Content":"control over our water. Uh, we"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:46:56.57","End":"2025-02-10T14:46:56.82","Content":"are one of only 3 states now,"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:46:58.872","End":"2025-02-10T14:46:59.122","Content":"uh, that don't assert primacy,"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:47:00.808","End":"2025-02-10T14:47:01.058","Content":"all the Western states do. New"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:47:02.576","End":"2025-02-10T14:47:02.826","Content":"Mexico, I believe New Hampshire"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:47:03.377","End":"2025-02-10T14:47:03.627","Content":"and Massachusetts are the three"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:47:05.312","End":"2025-02-10T14:47:05.562","Content":"states that don't, uh, exert"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:47:08.615","End":"2025-02-10T14:47:08.865","Content":"primacy. So that means that"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:47:10.851","End":"2025-02-10T14:47:11.101","Content":"issues involving surface water,"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:47:12.853","End":"2025-02-10T14:47:13.103","Content":"uh, that's covered by the"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:47:13.787","End":"2025-02-10T14:47:14.037","Content":"Federal Clean Water Act. I'll"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:47:14.455","End":"2025-02-10T14:47:14.705","Content":"talk about that in a minute, are"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:47:15.122","End":"2025-02-10T14:47:15.372","Content":"being"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:47:17.224","End":"2025-02-10T14:47:17.474","Content":"handled by the Dallas office of"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:47:19.46","End":"2025-02-10T14:47:19.71","Content":"the EPA under current um"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:47:21.795","End":"2025-02-10T14:47:22.045","Content":"Current regulatory oversight."},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:47:26.533","End":"2025-02-10T14:47:26.783","Content":"So, what is the clean Water Act"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:47:28.535","End":"2025-02-10T14:47:28.785","Content":"do. It deals with what are known"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:47:30.537","End":"2025-02-10T14:47:30.787","Content":"as waters of the United States"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:47:31.638","End":"2025-02-10T14:47:31.888","Content":"and this term, uh,"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:47:33.24","End":"2025-02-10T14:47:33.49","Content":"Basically has"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:47:36.81","End":"2025-02-10T14:47:37.06","Content":"Within the last 2 years in 2023,"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:47:39.346","End":"2025-02-10T14:47:39.596","Content":"2022, the US Supreme Court in"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:47:41.682","End":"2025-02-10T14:47:41.932","Content":"the sackett decision"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:47:43.35","End":"2025-02-10T14:47:43.6","Content":"substantially narrowed the"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:47:45.652","End":"2025-02-10T14:47:45.902","Content":"definition of what waters of the"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:47:47.354","End":"2025-02-10T14:47:47.604","Content":"United States copper, and this"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:47:50.791","End":"2025-02-10T14:47:51.041","Content":"is why 21 and 22 are important"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:47:52.826","End":"2025-02-10T14:47:53.076","Content":"and need to be addressed"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:47:54.561","End":"2025-02-10T14:47:54.811","Content":"together. I just want to read"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:47:55.329","End":"2025-02-10T14:47:55.579","Content":"from the Supreme Court's"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:47:57.097","End":"2025-02-10T14:47:57.347","Content":"decision, uh, because the issue"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:47:59.099","End":"2025-02-10T14:47:59.349","Content":"is whether wetlands that were"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:48:01.368","End":"2025-02-10T14:48:01.618","Content":"adjacent to uh waters of the"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:48:03.07","End":"2025-02-10T14:48:03.32","Content":"United States free-flowing"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:48:03.67","End":"2025-02-10T14:48:03.92","Content":"rivers. What's"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:48:05.339","End":"2025-02-10T14:48:05.589","Content":"task to determine whether they"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:48:07.141","End":"2025-02-10T14:48:07.391","Content":"are also included in terms of"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:48:09.376","End":"2025-02-10T14:48:09.626","Content":"the regulatory oversight. The"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:48:12.546","End":"2025-02-10T14:48:12.796","Content":"court took a much narrower"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:48:14.548","End":"2025-02-10T14:48:14.798","Content":"approach to the Clean Water Act,"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:48:16.583","End":"2025-02-10T14:48:16.833","Content":"and it, and I'll quote, it said"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:48:17.384","End":"2025-02-10T14:48:17.634","Content":"the Clean Water Act extends to"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:48:19.386","End":"2025-02-10T14:48:19.636","Content":"only wetlands that are quote as"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:48:20.854","End":"2025-02-10T14:48:21.104","Content":"a practical matter,"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:48:23.056","End":"2025-02-10T14:48:23.306","Content":"indistinguishable from waters of"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:48:24.858","End":"2025-02-10T14:48:25.108","Content":"the United States. This requires"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:48:26.827","End":"2025-02-10T14:48:27.077","Content":"the party asserting jurisdiction"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:48:28.562","End":"2025-02-10T14:48:28.812","Content":"to establish quote first that"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:48:29.43","End":"2025-02-10T14:48:29.68","Content":"the adjacent body of water"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:48:31.331","End":"2025-02-10T14:48:31.581","Content":"constitutes waters of the United"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:48:33.066","End":"2025-02-10T14:48:33.316","Content":"States. In other words, a"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:48:33.634","End":"2025-02-10T14:48:33.884","Content":"relatively"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:48:35.302","End":"2025-02-10T14:48:35.552","Content":"permanent body of water"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:48:37.071","End":"2025-02-10T14:48:37.321","Content":"connected to traditional"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:48:40.541","End":"2025-02-10T14:48:40.791","Content":"interstate navigable waters. And"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:48:41.308","End":"2025-02-10T14:48:41.558","Content":"second, that the wetland has a"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:48:43.577","End":"2025-02-10T14:48:43.827","Content":"continuous surface connection"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:48:44.178","End":"2025-02-10T14:48:44.428","Content":"with that water."},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:48:46.847","End":"2025-02-10T14:48:47.097","Content":"Making it difficult to determine"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:48:48.582","End":"2025-02-10T14:48:48.832","Content":"where the water ends and where"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:48:49.216","End":"2025-02-10T14:48:49.466","Content":"the wetland begins."},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:48:52.586","End":"2025-02-10T14:48:52.836","Content":"Well, this interpretation in the"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:48:54.555","End":"2025-02-10T14:48:54.805","Content":"Sackett case basically resulted"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:48:55.456","End":"2025-02-10T14:48:55.706","Content":"in about 95% of the"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:48:59.593","End":"2025-02-10T14:48:59.843","Content":"Water in New Mexico no longer"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:49:01.061","End":"2025-02-10T14:49:01.311","Content":"being covered by the Clean Water"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:49:04.798","End":"2025-02-10T14:49:05.048","Content":"Act and Senate Bill 22 is"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:49:05.299","End":"2025-02-10T14:49:05.549","Content":"putting the environment"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:49:07.101","End":"2025-02-10T14:49:07.351","Content":"department into regulatory"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:49:10.804","End":"2025-02-10T14:49:11.054","Content":"oversight for those 95%, um,"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:49:11.805","End":"2025-02-10T14:49:12.055","Content":"that are not covered. Why is"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:49:12.439","End":"2025-02-10T14:49:12.689","Content":"this important?"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:49:13.574","End":"2025-02-10T14:49:13.824","Content":"Uh, obviously,"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:49:19.113","End":"2025-02-10T14:49:19.363","Content":"Water is of critical importance"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:49:20.814","End":"2025-02-10T14:49:21.064","Content":"here in New Mexico. Experts are"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:49:23.083","End":"2025-02-10T14:49:23.333","Content":"predicting 25% less water in the"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:49:25.018","End":"2025-02-10T14:49:25.268","Content":"next 50 years, and"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:49:28.822","End":"2025-02-10T14:49:29.072","Content":"Again, both Senate Bill 21 and"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:49:31.291","End":"2025-02-10T14:49:31.541","Content":"22, Senate Bill 21, has, has the"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:49:33.06","End":"2025-02-10T14:49:33.31","Content":"Environment department asserting"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:49:35.028","End":"2025-02-10T14:49:35.278","Content":"the primacy to be able to"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:49:36.764","End":"2025-02-10T14:49:37.014","Content":"implement the Water Act and then"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:49:39.299","End":"2025-02-10T14:49:39.549","Content":"22 expands to allow us to cover"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:49:39.967","End":"2025-02-10T14:49:40.217","Content":"um"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:49:42.569","End":"2025-02-10T14:49:42.819","Content":"What are called ephemeral"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:49:44.805","End":"2025-02-10T14:49:45.055","Content":"streams and waterways, so those"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:49:46.84","End":"2025-02-10T14:49:47.09","Content":"that are not covered, I would"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:49:47.474","End":"2025-02-10T14:49:47.724","Content":"say the ones that had been"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:49:50.811","End":"2025-02-10T14:49:51.061","Content":"covered for 50 years from 72"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:49:52.88","End":"2025-02-10T14:49:53.13","Content":"until 2022, those were all"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:49:54.581","End":"2025-02-10T14:49:54.831","Content":"covered under the Clean Water"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:49:55.449","End":"2025-02-10T14:49:55.699","Content":"Act, but once the Supreme Court"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:49:58.552","End":"2025-02-10T14:49:58.802","Content":"narrowed the definition, it"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:49:59.353","End":"2025-02-10T14:49:59.603","Content":"shrunk it down substantially."},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:50:03.056","End":"2025-02-10T14:50:03.306","Content":"So, Mr. Chair, I can explain 22"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:50:04.792","End":"2025-02-10T14:50:05.042","Content":"highlights and then go through"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:50:06.627","End":"2025-02-10T14:50:06.877","Content":"the substitute, which I think on"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:50:09.296","End":"2025-02-10T14:50:09.546","Content":"21, so 22 basically has two"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:50:11.298","End":"2025-02-10T14:50:11.548","Content":"prongs, as I mentioned, uh,"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:50:13.1","End":"2025-02-10T14:50:13.35","Content":"prong number one is to deal with"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:50:15.402","End":"2025-02-10T14:50:15.652","Content":"those ephemeral waters that are"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:50:18.539","End":"2025-02-10T14:50:18.789","Content":"no longer covered, uh, by the,"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:50:20.808","End":"2025-02-10T14:50:21.058","Content":"um, Clean Water Act based on the"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:50:23.043","End":"2025-02-10T14:50:23.293","Content":"Sacket decision. The second"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:50:25.479","End":"2025-02-10T14:50:25.729","Content":"thing that it does, uh, is"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:50:28.582","End":"2025-02-10T14:50:28.832","Content":"create a new, and I can go"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:50:29.349","End":"2025-02-10T14:50:29.599","Content":"through the specifics of that,"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:50:30.017","End":"2025-02-10T14:50:30.267","Content":"but given the time, I think"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:50:30.617","End":"2025-02-10T14:50:30.867","Content":"we'll do that through."},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:50:32.553","End":"2025-02-10T14:50:32.803","Content":"The experts when we get to that"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:50:33.32","End":"2025-02-10T14:50:33.57","Content":"point. The second thing Senate"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:50:35.322","End":"2025-02-10T14:50:35.572","Content":"Bill 22 does, it deals with"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:50:38.525","End":"2025-02-10T14:50:38.775","Content":"groundwater protection, and it"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:50:39.293","End":"2025-02-10T14:50:39.543","Content":"provides authority to hold"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:50:41.295","End":"2025-02-10T14:50:41.545","Content":"polluters, and this is different"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:50:42.596","End":"2025-02-10T14:50:42.846","Content":"from surface water, but whole"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:50:43.33","End":"2025-02-10T14:50:43.58","Content":"polluters responsible for"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:50:45.099","End":"2025-02-10T14:50:45.349","Content":"groundwater pollution and soil"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:50:46.8","End":"2025-02-10T14:50:47.05","Content":"contamination that threatens"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:50:48.836","End":"2025-02-10T14:50:49.086","Content":"groundwater. It establishes"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:50:50.537","End":"2025-02-10T14:50:50.787","Content":"authority for the water quality"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:50:51.338","End":"2025-02-10T14:50:51.588","Content":"control commission to issue"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:50:53.307","End":"2025-02-10T14:50:53.557","Content":"rules and clarifies cleanup and"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:50:54.875","End":"2025-02-10T14:50:55.125","Content":"financial liability for"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:50:56.877","End":"2025-02-10T14:50:57.127","Content":"environmental contamination. It"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:50:58.846","End":"2025-02-10T14:50:59.096","Content":"creates a new fund. In effect,"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:50:59.513","End":"2025-02-10T14:50:59.763","Content":"this is a state super fund and"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:51:00.214","End":"2025-02-10T14:51:00.464","Content":"there's"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:51:03.05","End":"2025-02-10T14:51:03.3","Content":"Lots and on Wednesday we'll talk"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:51:05.319","End":"2025-02-10T14:51:05.569","Content":"about how we adopt that and, and"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:51:07.287","End":"2025-02-10T14:51:07.537","Content":"what's put in statute versus"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:51:09.022","End":"2025-02-10T14:51:09.272","Content":"what's going to be done in rule."},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:51:10.791","End":"2025-02-10T14:51:11.041","Content":"What I'd like to do, Mr. Chair,"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:51:11.425","End":"2025-02-10T14:51:11.675","Content":"is just before we go out to the"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:51:12.86","End":"2025-02-10T14:51:13.11","Content":"audience, I want to walk through"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:51:15.162","End":"2025-02-10T14:51:15.412","Content":"the judiciary substitute to 21,"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:51:16.563","End":"2025-02-10T14:51:16.813","Content":"because this is important"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:51:17.131","End":"2025-02-10T14:51:17.381","Content":"because it's changed"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:51:18.832","End":"2025-02-10T14:51:19.082","Content":"substantially from what was"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:51:20.834","End":"2025-02-10T14:51:21.084","Content":"introduced. It does carry over"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:51:22.803","End":"2025-02-10T14:51:23.053","Content":"the two amendments that were put"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:51:23.57","End":"2025-02-10T14:51:23.82","Content":"on in Senate conservation."},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:51:25.372","End":"2025-02-10T14:51:25.622","Content":"Number one, it removes the"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:51:28.575","End":"2025-02-10T14:51:28.825","Content":"phrase produced water, uh, and"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:51:29.376","End":"2025-02-10T14:51:29.626","Content":"other language from the"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:51:29.943","End":"2025-02-10T14:51:30.193","Content":"definition of pollutant."},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:51:30.944","End":"2025-02-10T14:51:31.194","Content":"Um"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:51:34.515","End":"2025-02-10T14:51:34.765","Content":"That this was causing a lot of"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:51:35.282","End":"2025-02-10T14:51:35.532","Content":"confusion that this might be"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:51:37.117","End":"2025-02-10T14:51:37.367","Content":"somehow a produced water bill,"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:51:39.386","End":"2025-02-10T14:51:39.636","Content":"it's not, uh, so it took that"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:51:43.323","End":"2025-02-10T14:51:43.573","Content":"language out. It also added the"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:51:45.359","End":"2025-02-10T14:51:45.609","Content":"in section, subsection E and"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:51:49.096","End":"2025-02-10T14:51:49.346","Content":"section 3, page 5, lines 13"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:51:51.365","End":"2025-02-10T14:51:51.615","Content":"through 25 and page 6 lines 1"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:51:53.4","End":"2025-02-10T14:51:53.65","Content":"through 20. It basically lists"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:51:55.102","End":"2025-02-10T14:51:55.352","Content":"all of the exemptions that"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:51:56.837","End":"2025-02-10T14:51:57.087","Content":"currently exist under the Clean"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:51:58.539","End":"2025-02-10T14:51:58.789","Content":"Water Act. What we're trying to"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:51:59.64","End":"2025-02-10T14:51:59.89","Content":"do is have a status quo"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:52:01.008","End":"2025-02-10T14:52:01.258","Content":"regulatory environment and as"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:52:01.708","End":"2025-02-10T14:52:01.958","Content":"originally"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:52:04.778","End":"2025-02-10T14:52:05.028","Content":"introduced, it didn't track"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:52:05.579","End":"2025-02-10T14:52:05.829","Content":"exactly. We lined it up to"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:52:06.113","End":"2025-02-10T14:52:06.363","Content":"track."},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:52:09.316","End":"2025-02-10T14:52:09.566","Content":"Um, the substitute adds a new"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:52:11.318","End":"2025-02-10T14:52:11.568","Content":"subsection B in section 4 to"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:52:12.853","End":"2025-02-10T14:52:13.103","Content":"clearly state that the water"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:52:14.555","End":"2025-02-10T14:52:14.805","Content":"quality control commission's"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:52:15.622","End":"2025-02-10T14:52:15.872","Content":"rules must include a public"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:52:17.391","End":"2025-02-10T14:52:17.641","Content":"notice process, specifically"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:52:19.193","End":"2025-02-10T14:52:19.443","Content":"including Indian nations, tribes"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:52:21.095","End":"2025-02-10T14:52:21.345","Content":"and pueblos. Uh, this came at"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:52:22.83","End":"2025-02-10T14:52:23.08","Content":"the request of the Tasuki"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:52:24.832","End":"2025-02-10T14:52:25.082","Content":"Pueblo, uh, wanted to make sure"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:52:26.6","End":"2025-02-10T14:52:26.85","Content":"that notice was part of the"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:52:27.401","End":"2025-02-10T14:52:27.651","Content":"bill. And so that's been added."},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:52:30.838","End":"2025-02-10T14:52:31.088","Content":"Uh the 4th change is section 4"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:52:34.908","End":"2025-02-10T14:52:35.158","Content":"subsection C deletes pay and"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:52:35.576","End":"2025-02-10T14:52:35.826","Content":"inserts support."},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:52:37.311","End":"2025-02-10T14:52:37.561","Content":"Uh, there's going to be a lot of"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:52:38.779","End":"2025-02-10T14:52:39.029","Content":"discussion and this bill goes to"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:52:39.546","End":"2025-02-10T14:52:39.796","Content":"Senate Finance. How are we going"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:52:41.081","End":"2025-02-10T14:52:41.331","Content":"to pay for this? Uh, it"},{"Begin":"2025-02-10T14:52:44.551","End":"2025-02-10T14:52:44.801","Content":"currently was designed to and"}]}